sign   Development The instructional design staff of LTS offers support for the use of quality design standards and best practices in course design for technology enhanced  blended  and fully online courses  This includes the exploration of collaborative tools  the redesign of courses to meet accessibility requirements  and the improvement of the course structure in general Equipment Lending LTS offers equipment for short term loan to both faculty and students Professional Development The LTS team provides trainings in various formats  We offer webinars and workshops on a variety of topics including all of the basic instructional tools supported at UIC  The goal of these sessions is to help instructors improve their use of technology by providing guidance on the use of best practices for teaching with technology  We also design tailored sessions for academic departments  Online video tutorials are also available on a wide range of topics through our Lynda com subscription trainings Community Engagement We continually strive to create a campus community that shares best practices for using technology for teaching and learning LTS uic edu Lecture Center E n t t tRoom E     west side of building Open     am to     pm Monday through Thursday and     am to     pm Friday during academic sessions Richard J  Daley Library n t t tRoom LIB        first floor at the south side of the IDEA Commons  t t tOpen weekdays     am to     pm Benjamin Goldberg Research Center  BGRC  n t t tRoom     By appointment only ITL LETS Service Catalog Service Catalog Service Categories Popular Services Popular Services Learning Management System G Suite  formerly Google Apps Exchange Box Lecture Capture Classrooms ACCC Service Desk Wireless Network Learning Technology Solutions Telecommunications  ACCC About ACCC Accessibility Resources Jobs News and Alerts Policies and Guidelines Telecom ACCC Newsletter Reports Quick Links Get started Activate UIC NetID Change password Create accounts Blackboar